The paper is about the optimization of artificial neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the adaptation of the neural network architecture, activation function, connection weights, and learning algorithm, which falls under the category of meta-learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also presents experimentation results related to convergence speed and generalization performance, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance of different learning algorithms for chaotic time series, which falls under the category of systems and control. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the theoretical background and design strategy of the proposed MLEANN framework, which falls under the category of neural information processing. Therefore, cs.NI (Neural Information Processing) is another likely sub-category.
